##Multiple items open
To allow multiple panels to be open at the same time, add attribute `data-multiple` to the component container.

{{/markdown}}
                    <div class="docu-example is-demo">
                        <h3 class="docu-example-title">Demo</h3>
                        <div>
                            {{#mergeJSON rb_accordion.default 'attrs: {"multiple": true}'}}
                                {{> rb_accordion }}
                            {{/mergeJSON}}
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="docu-example is-demo">
                        <h3 class="docu-example-title">Markup</h3>
{{#markdown}}
    <div class="rb-accordion" data-module="accordion" data-multiple="true">
        ...
    </div>
{{/markdown}}
                    </div>

                    <hr>

                    <div class="docu-example">
                        <h3 class="docu-example-title">JS Options</h3>
 {{#markdown}}
| Option | Value | Default | Description
| ------------- |-------------|
| `multiple`  | Boolean | false | Allowed multiple panels to be open at the same time. If `true` then `toggle` is also automatically set to `true`.
| `toggle`  | Boolean | false | Whether a panel button toggles the state of a panel.
| `selectedIndex`  | Number | 1 | The initially opened index. If no panel with the class `is-open` was found. If no panel should be opened by default use -1.
| `animation`  | String | ' ' | Possible animations: `adaptHeight` or `slide`. These should be combined with CSS transitions or animations.
 {{/markdown}}
